    "body": "Hi,\r\nI have installed Gromacs 2020 version with following configuration-\r\nCase 1. Manually- with Intel 2018.5, Intel-mkl , simd=AVX2_256, without CUDA support.\r\nCase 2. compiled Gromacs with spack utility with below variant-\r\n       \"gromacs@2020%intel@18.0.5 build_type=RelWithDebInfo ~cuda~double~double_precision~hwloc~mdrun_only+mpi+openmp~plumed+rdtscp+shared simd=AVX2_256 arch=linux-centos7-skylake_avx512\"\r\n\r\nAfter Running same benchmark for both cases, Manually installed Gromacs uses all availabe cores with 100% utilization while spack built gromacs uses only 50% of available core . \r\n\r\nCan you please help in this matter?\r\n\r\nThanks in advance\r\n\r\n",
